scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This subseries contains IBT airline division materials related to specific airlines and air cargo companies dating from the 1990s and 2000s.

Airlines and companies included are Air Transport International, Air Tran Airways, Bonk Air Transportation, Centurion Air Cargo, Challenge Air Cargo, Chautauqua Air, Comair/Delta Airlines, EG & G Technical Services, Executive Jet Aviation, ExpressJet, Frontier Airlines, Gemini Air Cargo, Go Jet Airlines, Grand Aire Express, Great Lakes Aviation, Kalitta Air, Mid-Atlantic Airways, NetJets, North American Airlines, Northwest Airlines, Piedmont/Allegheny Airlines, Pinnacle Air, PSA Airlines, Republic Airways, Swissport USA, Transmeridian Airlines, Trans States Airlines, U.S. Airways, World Airways, and Zantop International.

Specific materials include correspondence, memoranda, contracts/negotiation, financial information, newsletters, news clippings, seniority lists, National Mediation Board materials, health/welfare information, union election ballots, union representation applications, Central States Pension Fund materials, grievances, FAQs, handbooks/manuals, flyers, and other miscellaneous items.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: This subseries is arranged alphabetically by airline/company name. Materials for each company have yet to be further organized.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This subseries contains subject files related to the Teamsters Airline Division dating from 1980-2008. Included are Airline Division budget, training, health and welfare, arbitration and grievance materials, as well as materials from various aviation and flight attendant unions, Teamsters local unions, the National Mediation Board, the Federal Aviation Administration, and the Transportation Security Administration.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The materials in this series include the transcripts of proceedings of the Teamsters National Bakery Conference. The dates range from 1942-1973. There are some gaps between the years where no transcript of proceedings exists.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: The IBT Warehouse Division provides a variety of support services to Teamsters local unions representing members employed in warehousing, distribution, food processing and related industries. This includes job classifications such as drivers, lift truck operators, equipment operators, food processing workers and clerical workers. The Division was formed in September 1948 at a conference held in Chicago that drew close to 300 attendees. The Warehouse Division assists local unions in designing and executing successful bargaining and campaign strategies. It is also responsible for conducting production standards reports and time studies.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The Materials of this series include proceedings and annual reports. They range from 1948 to 1981, and represent the history of the National Warehouse Conferences of the International Brotherhood of Teamsters . The early proceedings contain transcripts of the meetings while the later proceedings contain the remarks of various speakers, sometimes only in part. The annual reports (from 1954-1957) contain summaries of the year's activities, along with lists of various officers and committee members.
